         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Yale Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection (MS 1258).   This collection is an artificial collection of correspondence, writings, diaries, and memorabilia relating to Yale University, its officials and employees, faculty, students, and related topics.</p>
         <p>HM 268 only consists of Nathaniel W. Taylor's journal of a voyage to Hurd's Island, 1857-1859, in Series I</p>  
